{
  "text": "Immigrant entrepreneurship 1) creates job opportunities for individuals who are overlooked by mainstream labour markets, 2) decreases competition with native-born workers, develops entrepreneurial role models, and 3) provides a way for immigrants to increase earnings [CITATION_1] . Through this lens, immigrant entrepreneurs (IE) are often characterised as experiencing barrier-based (push) self-employment (e.g. [CITATION_2] ).",
